  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>What is a Fixed Deposit (FD)?</h2>
          <p>A Fixed Deposit is a financial instrument offered by banks and NBFCs where you invest a lump sum for a predetermined period at a fixed interest rate. FDs are one of the safest investment options in India, offering guaranteed returns unaffected by market fluctuations. They are ideal for conservative investors, emergency fund parking, and senior citizens looking for regular income.</p>
          <p>FD interest rates currently range from 6.5% to 8.50% p.a. depending on the bank and tenure. Senior citizens typically receive an additional 0.25-0.50% p.a. FDs also qualify for tax-saving under Section 80C (5-year lock-in tax-saver FDs).</p>

          <h3>How is FD Maturity Calculated?</h3>
          <p>FD returns are calculated using compound interest, typically compounded quarterly. The formula is: Maturity Amount = P × (1 + r/n)^(n×t), where P is the principal, r is the annual interest rate, n is the compounding frequency (4 for quarterly), and t is the tenure in years. The interest earned is simply Maturity Amount minus the Principal.</p>

          <div class="calculator-widget">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-piggy-bank" style="color: var(--primary); margin-right: 8px;"></i> FD Calculator</h3>
            <div class="calc-form-group">
              <label for="depositAmount">Deposit Amount: <strong id="depositDisplay">₹5,00,000</strong></label>
              <input type="range" id="depositAmount" min="10000" max="10000000" value="500000" step="10000">
              <div class="calc-range-labels"><span>₹10,000</span><span>₹1,00,00,000</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-form-group">
              <label for="interestRate">Interest Rate (% p.a.): <strong id="rateDisplay">7.25%</strong></label>
              <input type="range" id="interestRate" min="5" max="9" value="7.25" step="0.05">
              <div class="calc-range-labels"><span>5%</span><span>9%</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-form-group">
              <label for="tenure">Tenure (Years): <strong id="tenureDisplay">3 Years</strong></label>
              <input type="range" id="tenure" min="1" max="10" value="3" step="1">
              <div class="calc-range-labels"><span>1 Year</span><span>10 Years</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-result">
              <div class="calc-result-item"><span class="calc-label">Maturity Amount</span><span class="calc-value" id="maturityAmount">₹6,20,118</span></div>
              <div class="calc-result-item"><span class="calc-label">Interest Earned</span><span class="calc-value" id="interestEarned">₹1,20,118</span></div>
              <div class="calc-result-item"><span class="calc-label">Effective Yield</span><span class="calc-value" id="effectiveYield">7.45%</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>FD Rate Comparison — April 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Bank</th><th>1 Year</th><th>3 Years</th><th>5 Years</th><th>Senior Citizen (5Y)</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>SBI</td><td>6.80%</td><td>7.00%</td><td>6.50%</td><td>7.00%</td></tr>
              <tr><td>HDFC Bank</td><td>6.60%</td><td>7.10%</td><td>7.00%</td><td>7.50%</td></tr>
              <tr><td>ICICI Bank</td><td>6.70%</td><td>7.10%</td><td>7.00%</td><td>7.50%</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Bajaj Finance</td><td>7.40%</td><td>7.90%</td><td>7.75%</td><td>8.25%</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Post Office</td><td>6.90%</td><td>7.00%</td><td>7.50%</td><td>7.50%</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Why Use Our FD Calculator?</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> <strong>Accurate Compounding</strong> — Calculates quarterly compounding as used by most banks</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> <strong>Rate Comparison</strong> — Compare FD rates across SBI, HDFC, ICICI, Bajaj Finance, and more</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> <strong>Tax Planning</strong> — Understand TDS impact and 80C benefit on 5-year tax-saver FDs</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> <strong>Senior Citizen Rates</strong> — Check additional 0.25-0.50% benefit for senior citizens</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> <strong>Goal Planning</strong> — Calculate how much to invest today to reach a target amount by a future date</li>
